<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="L" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="London" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">London,</orth> the capital of England: <bibl n="shak. jn 5.1.31" default="NO" valid="yes">John V, 1, 31</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 3.3.208" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 3, 208</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 3.4.90" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 4, 90</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 3.4.90" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 4, 90</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r2 5.2.3" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 3</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 5.3.6" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 5.6.7" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 6, 7</bibl> etc. Used as a fem. in <bibl n="shak. h5 5.0" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 V Chor.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h5 5.0" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 V Chor.</bibl> <cit><quote>Welcome to L., to your chamber,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 3.1.1" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 1, 1</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>through L. gates,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.8.24" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 8, 24</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>in L. streets,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 5.5.77" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 V, 5, 77</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.8.47" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 8, 47</bibl>. <cit><quote>at L. bridge,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.1.23" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A III, 1, 23</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.4.49" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 4, 49</bibl>. <cit><quote>set L. bridge on fire,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.6.16" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 6, 16</bibl></cit> (it being, at that time, made of wood). <cit><quote>sitting upon L. stone,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.6.2" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 6, 2</bibl></cit> (probably a monument called so).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>